caption: You will not be disappointed no matter what meal (brunch, dinner) or dish you choose.

A Great spot. The only reason I don't go there more often is because the weekends are crazy. And their coffee....they Casually make the Best Coffee. I just had the jerk pork bowl. Once again no complaints. A great spot.
loved this place! great food + atmosphere.. would recommend it to anyone, local or visiting 🤎
Great food and great service with a playlist that makes you move while enjoying the grub. Socially distance with out door dining too. Highly recommend!
The food was scrumpdillycious! The service spot on. I'll be back!
One of the best Soul restaurants near Grand Army. Survived CV19 and is still going strong. Local, great food, new surprises, and some of the best value in the area.
Great hodge-podge atmosphere. We almost mistook it for it being closed down, but enjoyed some of the best brunch we've had for a while. Pancakes, Chicken strips, home fries are all top notch.
The shrimp was bland and the drinks so watered down.
Amazing black owned restaurant. Great food. Great service. Great ambiance.
My go too spot. Rum punches on point. Miss the menu pre covid. Had almost everything on the menu. Miss my hang out spot for breakfast, brunch & dinner.

Had a wonderful outdoor dining experience here for lunch. The server was friendly, food was delicious (I had the split pea soup). As far as covid protocols go, they were on top of things. Server wore a mask the whole time, we got disposable utensils wrapped up, seating was six feet apart. Well done guys. Make sure to give them your business. Keep our local restaurants alive!
Good
The best egg/cheddar/ mushroom sandwich Ive tasted in a long time! And the ginger tea was delicious!
Fun soul food spot. Great cocktails. Vegetarian chili is a lot soupier than expected and the Mac n cheese is casserole style and not the cheesy gooey type that you might be expecting.
Neighborhood staple!
All good
Met the owner when she first opened. This is a small woman-owned business and LOVE that she's still in business even during these tough times. Excellent food even with a scaled back menu.
Food is great
Love the hot Ginger Aide

This place has a great chicken sandwich. Definitely the best in my neighborhood! But that's neither here nor there. I'm here to say that my cat is an absolute terror whenever we order from this place. To date, she has stolen both half of a hamburger and a block of Mac and cheese out of closed containers. Fortunately, she is terrible at thievery, and didn't manage to eat much of it. I was very sad about the loss of my mac and cheese during this traumatic event. I was looking forward to eating that. Oh well. A great dinner nonetheless.
really good food, service was excellent and staff was really good.

Invited by a friend this was my first time dining here. We chose the pancakes with the Chantilly cream on the side. The pancakes were great-firm on the outside with a soft warm center. The Chantilly cream was a nice addition as I am accustomed to maple syrup with my pancakes. It added a sweet creamy flavor to top off the pancakes.  The service has more to be desired. When asked for an extra serving of chantilly cream, we waited and waited. It was not presented at the table until all of the pancakes had been eaten, what are we to do with the cream then? Overall, however, I would certainly dine here again to sample the variety of foods the menu has to offer!
Not good

Found this place today for brunch and it was amazing! The service is incredible the vibes are gorgeous good music and ambiance. The covid precautions were great including hand sanitizer at the table and staff wearing mask. Most of all the Food had great flavor!!  Soo good!! I never leave reviews but i had to!! This is a win for Brooklyn!!

Ya’ll. There’s no place like home. And Cheryl’s makes you feel like you’re home. Looking for a great place to brunch? Look no further. Breakfast? Yup! Dinner?! Get there! I try to always go to a new place to eat, we’re in New York... but whenever anyone comes to visit, it’s Cheryl’s. Amazing service. Amazing food. Amazing vibe. 11/10 would recommend. Why’re you still reading? Go NOW!!!!

The food, service, ambiance and music was just what I needed. Enjoyed my birthday lunch and wish I had the time to enjoy my surprise dessert sitting down.  Thank you for the birthday kindness.  Shout out to Juan and his colleague!
Love their backyard
Great Food, Nice spot!
Cheryl's is my go to brunch spot in my neighborhood. 10/10 food, drinks, and atmosphere even in these crazy covid times
Went here for an impromptu brunch and the offerings were pretty on par w what I expect of a brunch menu.

Its been a place I have been wanting to visit.  It is charming.  I love the backyard space the food is amazing and so are the drinks.  Made our current situation feel as if it does not exist for that time. .❤
Wings were two big but great location and great tasting food.
Delicious food. Friendly staff. Nice backyard seating area.
The food here is absolutely amazing. OMG where have been to missing out on all of this. Their menu is freaking amazing, you must check this place out.
Love coming her for a relaxed vibe! The gingerade is a must for a refreshing summer pick me up ❤️
Wonderful folks, went to pick up takeout and Cheryl was keeping an eye on everything at a table near the counter.  Fried chicken sandwich was delicious, as were the side salad and Cajun wings!
Favorite near the Brooklyn museum. Quaint but food is delicious and occasionally you might get a little music!
Needs more seating, wait is crazy for Sunday brunch. Good was okay
Good food good service A nice intimate space the front space opens in the warm weather and there's an outdoor backyard garden! Prices reasonable as well!
Great atmosphere, excellent and service.
Delicious food! All of it. When I called to ask about the wait they said they would hold a table for me, which I was so pleasantly surprised about.
Good food and decent service, depending on the waitress
Great food, top notch staff and super chill atmosphere.
Great food! Small and intimate place
Delicious food and very friendly staff
Delicious french fries!!  I would have given it five stars, but they want to charge for refills on soda.  Booooo.

You can always count on friendly service at Cheryl's, even though it may come at the expense of a long wait (especially for weekend brunch). The space is small, but if you're used to communal style public spaces with strangers, you'll do just fine (note: the tables aren't communal style, but you're close enough to others that it may feel that way). The food is fantastic, and mimosas are divine. Adding some vegan options to the menu would be great! Thanks for being a lovely establishment in our neighborhood.
Delicious and cozy.
One of the best pork chops in New York.
It was great as usual. I think it time to expand the restaurant. So much people eat their that it is super crowded. Just a suggestion.
Lovely Saturday morning brunch for three at this tiny establishment. Friendly staff, tasty food and reasonable prices. That’s a win win for me!

Best world cuisine restaurant in this part of Brooklyn, no contest. Backyard garden open un summer, under the trees. Great Caribbean-inspired dishes, generous cocktails, decent wine list, warm friendly atmosphere, and the kind of diverse dining crowd that makes me eminently thankful to be living in Brooklyn.  Chef Cheryl is all about love and good food. I don't get over here near often enough.

Inattentive wait staff. Nice ambiance. Quiet music - you can have a conversation without raising your voice.  Reasonable food at reasonable prices. Good turkey sandwich. Good french toast. They didn't have grilled chicken for the grilled chicken sandwich on the menu at noon on a weekday. The home fries were overly soggy. The ginger ale left something to be desired
Pea soup is delicious!
Decidedly Delicious
Delicious and great service! Cheryl is v welcoming. Also nice for a happy hour drink.
Food is great, but the service is horrible. Used to be my favorite brunch spot. Gotta fix these issues...
Great food and atmosphere.
Great neighborhood spot! Came for lunch and will be back.
Delicious food friendly staff and good atmosphere.
Great Brooklyn address for a brunch or snack

Small setting with close seats, but considering how crowded at the time we didn't have to wait. Good coffee and one of the better Bloody Mary's I've had, included with brunch.  Had carmelized apples and brie omelet and brioche French toast with fresh cream.  So good, we ordered a third plate of eggs and bacon to share.  Not expensive at all.

Decor was nice, steak was good but not very Bulgogi flavored. The macaroni was good and their vibe was very laid back. Good for steak, good vibes and overall nice food spot. I’m not entirely sure that I’d call it soul food by many folks standards but it’s a solid food place!

Yum yum just yum I love this place it’s totally worth the wait which is kinda long but the food and the atmosphere is so chill calm and did I mention the food is delicious totally recommend for brunch or regular day dining
The turkey sandwich had one slice of boars head turkey in it with a lot of lettuce. On the positive side, the staff were nice and friendly.
Went here for brunch and it was good. The wait wasn't terrible and the service was good. No complaints!
The food , the music, the hot sauce, the decor, the people...

(Translated by Google) Truly delicious brunch, with coffee and juice included in the price of the dishes. Absolutely to try the pancakes!  (Original) Brunch veramente squisito, con caffè e succo inclusi nel prezzo dei piatti. Assolutamente da provare i pancakes!

Great food, I had the Escovitch fish (fresh and delicious) and one of the best run punches I’ve had, strong and yummy! Service can be a bit slow, but it’s worth the wait, I’ll be back! (Tip: Skip the Mac and cheese).

I had the absolute best hot n' boozy hot chocolate here after walking through the Brooklyn Botanic Garden and also filled up on some seriously delicious black bean soup. This is a really cozy spot with super friendly and helpful wait staff and a great menu.
Everything was great!
A hidden gem! The food was great and the service was outstanding!
The BEST spot for brunch in Prospect Park. Amazing staff, amazing food, and amazing service.
FANTASTIC FOOD! The wait was well worth it! Service is superb, the smiles I got from staff at this establishment kept me smiling for about a week! #love #cherylsglobalsoul
Busy, but because the food is good and the service was pleasant.
The food was AMAZING!!!!!

Cuban Black Bean Soup. Bruce (my uncle's name btw) Hot Chocolate and a Mimosa... Cheryl's Global Soul is the place for a fantastic meal. I keep coming here every time I come to #NYC... just can't help myself.... lolz #CherylsGlobalSoul
Had delicious poached eggs with salmon hash. A little bland but perfectly filling.  Would have liked a slice of fruit garnish with it. Small place w/ tight seating.

Nice stop for family lunch.  Cheryl's offered lunch and breakfast options,  which met the needs of all in our group. We were there the last hour for lunch so some items were out of stock.  Great staff!
Quaint spot, sits approximately 50.Very popular, be prepared to wait approximately 30 minutes.Excellently food, super fluffy pancakes. I tried the salmon hash, it was very good, definitely recommend!
Their cocktail, The Brooklyn, is amazing they offer during their happy hour.
Always great food and service the fish and her steak is delicious!!! The breadpudding is EVERYTHING!! And do not leave without having the rum punch! Our waiter Marcos was the best!
My wife's favorite breakfast spot!

Food and prices were average. Somehow I was expecting more than diner food. The guy who seemed like the owner was very friendly, but our waitress was cold and almost nasty with her dismissive attitude. Everything was just fine, but the poor service was aggravating. It's been a while since I was treated like that and there are too many better places around.
It's a lovely place with a cozy feel. The staff was friendly and food was delicious! Had breakfast there and will definitely be going back for their happy hour and dinner.
Seriously the Best.
Love the salmon
Great neighborhood spot. Love their egg sandwiches.

Food was awesome! The tea and lemonade combination was refreshing! The calamari with the chili sauce was perfect ; sweet with a tiny amount of spice! I can sing home about the pork chops with roasted potatoes and string beans; the sauce was stupendously delicious! Ode to the Chef!!! Their food blends and tastes tantalize the taste bud!!!
Great drinks and specialty dishes. Get there at happy hour to enjoy there creative mixed drinks
The best Steak and the best burger in the world
Appetizers were delicious. The main courses and drinks were mediocre and the dessert was not worth getting. It's a very quaint and quiet place. The waiters were nice.
Food is so good and staff was great!

Everything about this place is wonderful! The food was incredible. I was in a large party so everyone shared their meals. Everything was outstanding: jerk chicken, steak, sake-glazed salmon, mac n cheese, roasted beet salad, fish soup, fried catfish... Everything was prepared with thought and care. The spice profile is perfect. Ambiance, wait staff, all was perfect. And there was even live music. I can't wait to go back.
Would definitely recommend trying this place. Fantastic character, delicious dishes, fantastic service. They never disappoint.
Great food

Terrible service and rude waitress! I went with my family because my daughter was in town from college and our brunch was ruined due to horrible customer service. Both the woman and the man there did not care about customers. How can the owner Cheryl Smith allow such people to run her restaurant. She should be made aware of how her customers are treated. I ordered brunch and received my coffee and drink all together. When I tried my coffee it was cold and I told the waitress my coffee is cold can I get another one and she said “you will have to pay” I said ok never mind. We were done eating and I could live without coffee for a day. What really bothered me was her sarcastic comment which was so unecessary. “The nature of coffee is for it to get cold” I let it go but it really bothered me because it is not how you should treat customers. She could have asked would you like me to warm it for you. That would have been nice. When I asked to speak with the manager she said “ I am the manager” I was in shock. I didn’t want to speak with her because she was rude. I spoke to the man who was seating everyone and he seemed like he didn’t care as well and said our policy is that We don’t give refill on coffee . I get that. The point is the way I was spoken to is unacceptable. The waitress chimed in and said “she wants free coffee” “Don’t come back here”  to me infront of my kids. My seven year old was scared and said she was a mean and rude lady and told me let’s get out of here. My college daughter was upset that our family brunch was ruined by this waitress. It was embarrassing to me the ways she spoke to me infront of all the customers and my family. I was treated with no respect as a customer. I will never go back to this place no matter how good the food maybe it sure ruined everything. First of all it’s small, there is a long wait to be seated, service is terrible. Like someone else said there are other places in the neighborhood who deserves my money . Not some place that doesn’t care about their customers. Not worth my time and energy.

The food was ok.  The service was terrible.   The waitress is rude and nasty.  When our coffee was brought at the beginning of the meal and we wanted it at the end, she told us you only get one cup of coffee.  We told her our coffee is cold, she sarcastically said that is the nature of coffee.  Really?  Is that how you talk to customers?? When we spoke to the manager about it, she chimed in,"please don't come back".  Don't worry we won't.  Sorry but there is good food at plenty of other places throughout Brooklyn.  Don't waste your time with the terrible service here.
username: Pokemon Hunters with Steez and Snorlax

caption: Great breakfast spot!!

We went on a field trip to the Brooklyn Museum and we were recommended different local places to eat, Cheryl’s was one of them. We were told to call in advance so that we would have our food before we drove back to our school which is about two hours away. My friend and I called at 11:30 with our order and were told to pick it up at 12. At 12:00 we went to pick up our order and they had messed it up completely. We had to wait ANOTHER HOUR before we got our food to go and by this time we were late to our bus, causing ALL 40 KIDS ON IT TO BE LATE TO SCHOOL’S END AND THEIR AFTER SCHOOL OBLIGATIONS. We were very vocal about needed to leave ASAP but everyone who came after us proceeded to get their orders BEFORE we got our corrected one. One of the most frustrating experiences I’ve had in NYC and will definitely NEVER go back again. Obviously needs more staffing because it was a mess in there with two people trying to take and serve all the to go and I’m house orders while the guy working kept on whispering the f word every 5 minutes about how many people were there. Props to the blue haired girl though, thank you for being very apologetic and kind to my friend and I during our time of extreme frustration.
The service is of elegant standard. Definitely recommend it.
Nice brunch after a good bike ride at the park. Excellent service and loved the patio!
Food was good, drinks were good, nice ambiance, friendly people (customers and staff), great community spot.

Nice spot. Great food. Nice drinks. They didn't have everything in stock in this Friday so there were a lot of substitutions, on the bar. ... Even on one of their featured cocktails. Other than that the people were very nice and tried to work it out. I would still go back.

Very friendly staff food is yummy. Only thing for me is that the pancakes have gotten smaller than usual. Not worth the price. They're good but not worth the price anymore unless they make them a little bigger.
Every time we come here it’s an amazing experience and meal. It’s a fave!
Food and Service was Great
Food and service was incredible. Fluffiest pancakes ive ever seen.
Sit out back and forget you are in the city.  It's simple and lovely. Yum!
Love that Bread Pudding
I visited in July 2018. Good food and good service from a waitress from Germany. Don't let the exterior scare you
cozy and friendly. their pancakes are a must get. we went there three times during our stay in the area. couldn't resist. Still craving those pancakes!
My longtime friend took me out for brunch. The food was great.

Food was excellent. I ordered the Brioche French Toast with Caramelized Apples, and Chantilly Cream and my fiancee ordered the Norwegian Smoked Salmon Platter. Their homemade Chantilly cream is very flavorful. Unfortunately, the service was very sub-par.  It took the hostess 10 min to greet us and then sit us at a table (there were open tables). Then it took another 10 min to be greeted by a server. Then after the meal was completed it took over 15 min to get the check back from the server. All around the service was very slow and they weren't that busy which was very frustrating. However, I'm willing to give them another try for that french toast. :)
The pancakes were amazing!  Loved the nova and scrambled eggs.  Delish!
NOTE: they open at 8am but don’t serve breakfast till 9am. Weird times.
Brunch pre-fix is top class

Very nice honey restaurant  , my only issue  was the  coffee  that was served  coffee drippings  or stains was all over the  side of the  mugs and the milk served in paper cups. Other  than  that the food was great  and staff was friendly  and nice.
I love their back patio.  I rarely get to Brooklyn, but I plan on going here again.
I love Cheryl's Global Soul. The food is very tasty and of high quality. Ambience is relaxed and casual during the day which is when I usually eat there.
It was a good experience food was good
Serice was good, keep thinking I received a bad batch of pancakes
This place never disappoints and the last time I went Cheryl herself got on the mic to sing with the band. So much fun
Awesome - a real find!
Great food, great service and atmosphere. Definitely coming back again
The food was absolutely delicious and the garden was delightful

Came not on very busy day. Waited 45 minutes to get pretty mediocre burger and fries with a hair. Suspect they forgot to submit order to the kitchen until reminded after half hour of waiting, since other customer who arrived later already got served and finished meal by the time we received ours. Not a word of apology from staff about delay. However, they remembered to include mandatory 18% tip for this level of service. Was it worth it? No. Would not recommend. Skip and go some place else
Great hang out spot with a chill vibe and good food. Perfect for a friendly dinner and conversation or a first date.

THESE PEOPLE ARE RUDE, AGGRESSIVE, OVER CHARGING FOR FRIES, RUN OUT BEHIND CUSTOMERS ASKING FOR A TIP. SAYING I HOPE YOU ENJOYED YOUR MEAL BUT YOU NEVER GIVE A TIP . THIS WAS THE OWNER OF THE PLACE SON OR SOMETHING LIKE THAT . HE WAS ALREADY GUVEN A TIP, BUT MY FRIEND GIVE ANOTHER TIP . I THINK THAT THEY ARE RACIST AS WELL.

Unprofessional and rude. The service was good except for the fact that they totally left out two parts of my order. Whatever that was resolved. The problem comes when the waiter chased me and my friend out the door like we stole something saying “hey ladies did you guys enjoy yourself because you didn’t leave a tip”. We left a tip lol. My friends order was 9.50 (pancakes) and she charged her card 15 dollars to include tip. I still have the dude an extra 4 dollars at the door when he stopped us and he didn’t even say thank you. I don’t even leave reviews but that was super rude. I was actually shocked that’s never happened to me before and it’s unacceptable.

The food was very very good! I ordered quite a few things.  Though, I was a bit disappointed by the male waiter. He gave me that “I’ll give poor service to the younger person because they aren’t going to tip” vibe while waiting on me. I usually tip pretty well, and I still did.  He also scratched his balls after he put in another order for someone else. Also, I was a bit put off by his short shorts that looked like work out shorts. All I could think of is who is this sweaty grown a** man waiting on me. He wasn’t sweaty, but that’s all I could think about. I’ve always wondered why businesses have dress codes restricting workout clothes, but today I got it! And like I said, I’m young!  Suggestion for the kitchen: When a customer orders a sandwich to go, do not put it in a spacey box. By the time the customer gets home, it will be a tossed salad!!  Compliments to the owner: Yass auntie!! You are doing super well!! I love to see black people thrive! The food was just as good as Toms. Overall decor and customer base made me feel comfortable. You supersede Toms by 1,000pts.  You also have many savvy  customers! Thank you for a food experience!
Party of 20 in the garden. One waitress singlehandedly took orders, pleasant, and accommodating. Food 4 stars.
Best brunch in Brooklyn at a price you literally can’t find anywhere else in the city.
The food was amazing as always and the service was excellent!
Great happy hour from 12-7. $5 drinks!
Nice food and drinks!!!
Split pea soup and grilled burger was just excellent.
Friendly place for tasty breakfast
Great brunch spot in Brooklyn
good pricing for good food. My only gripe would be that they don't automatically give you butter with your pancakes, you have to ask for it.
Excellent food at reasonable prices...Stellar service!!!...Outdoor patio is quiet and nicely situated, magnificent for large groups...
I come here at least once a month. I just love their brunch, and even their dinner is amazing too.

A very cozy place for breakfast & Lunch in Brooklyn. The staff is so good with the customer service that you'll feel well attended and tentative..... definitely worth a visit for at the least a cup of coffee. The day I visited, It was raining in Brooklyn, and this place saved my morning. I would unquestionably come back.  FYI - You can't just walk as this place is popular you either make reservations or get ready to wait !! It's a good 20- 30 min wait time.

Literally come here almost every weekend for the brunch deal with coffee and bloody Mary or mimosa. We love the staff, the ambiance, and the food! Everything is delicious, but our favorites are the Sunday Pancakes or 3 Eggs Breakfast with bacon.
Really good food and great service.
Great food and  service
I love this place!!
Great brunch; attentive staff, cool crowd.
Great food, lovely backyard, wonderful drinks.
Never disappointed by the food at Cheryls! The service is attentive, quick and very friendly.
The service was very poor. The servers were rude. 😄👎
Food was spectacular as well as the ambiance! Such a cute spot with great brunch picks! I had the lox plate and it was just so fresh and delicious!
My local oasis. Brunch is particularly good, simple and affordable. In the summer eating outside under the trees is just delightful.

The service here is horrible. The waitresses were INATTENTIVE, INHOSPITABLE and SLOW. I say slow because I had to go and fetch a waitress in order to even be serviced. After 20 mins and no one asking to take even a drink order it seemed a little ridiculous. On top of that my order was not taken correctly as i was missing food. With all that being said, the food was actually delicious and well worth the price. But the service was just terrible. Wish i had read more into the reviews as it seems to be a common theme. I think service is as important as food, i want to feel welcomed and have a good time at a place im spending my money. If you come here I'll tell you the pancakes the porridge and the french toast are good. But make sure you track the waiters and waitresses because you will spend time waiting for no reason.

Saturday Brunch is all the wow. All Kinds of Beautiful People in door out door delight. I choose to eat inside, my First time their and now is my Favorite place to eat in Bklyn. My Beautiful Future brought me to this place her and her Friends, Cousin eat at all the time.  My Meal was to Die 4, Cheese Egg Omelet with Turkey Sausage
Ate there twice, dinner was fantastic. The menu is limited and no specials offered but you will enjoy their options.

I went to have a simple breakfast and was sadly disappointed. The pancakes had no flavor and were very small, especially considering that the client dining beside me had ones that were normal size, which were twice the size I had. (We joked about it) Also, the chicken sausage was deeply burnt. That’s all I had, and both items were a dud. Also, I was ignored completely once more customers came in. I usually don’t post reviews, but this place left a lot to be desired.
This place is great!!. The food a delicious; the place is well beautiful and very inviting. The people and the area is diverse. I'm definitely going back soon.

Misleading business hours. The place is "open" at 8am, but the kitchen opens at 9. So... It's kinda open but not really, but you can seat but you can't eat. It's more like 8am is when the crew comes in.  People, a restaurant without an open kitchen is just a room. Don't say you're open if you're not.  Food is great, tho.
Service is great. Food is wonderful!

My dad and I arrived there in a windy-rainy day and we got wet from the top to the bottom. We were tired and hungry but luckily the service was pretty fast and we got what we ordered in a few moments. This is a good place for bunch of friends chilling out and have a little drinks!
There were bugs in my food. The home fries were greecy and oily.
I really like this place, simple, friendly, nice outdoor and the food was tasty and very quick even as the place was filling up. Highly recommend.
We went for brunch, food was good. People waiting  to get in
Always wonderful food. I have never been disappointed. Cheryl and her staff are very nice.
Very chilled homey style restaurant. I had nova in scrambled eggs for breakfast. A nice choice if you are too early to hit the Brooklyn museum.
Good food. Good service.  Nice neighborhood!
Was told it would be a 45 min wait.  Ended up being 1:20.  We wouldn’t have waited had we known it was that long.  Food was decent but not worth that massive wait.

They have a nice restaurant but not accommodating I traveled from Philadelphia  to have brunch with friends they ordered my meal for me but it was not at all what I wanted I order an omelette with diced tomatoes and green peppers in the potatoes. They wouldn't put the tomatoes in the eggs but gave me two slices of tomatoes warmed up and provided a salad with my breakfast???  I told them this is not what I ordered and I'm not satisfied they said they couldn't remove my meal because I'm not satisfied they only took half off...I ended up not ordering anything because of the lack of customer service.
Good food. The pancakes were excellent. The Saturday brunch wait was kinda long though, 40 mins. So take that into account for planning ahead.

First time here, but I’ll be back again and again! Great service, food and personnel! Oh, did I forget the other customers real cool!  Just an overall down home place with down home people!  Happy Memorial Day!!

No bad experience or anything. Came in, saw the menu and left. I dont grasp the concept of this being a soul food restaurant with no soul... nothing on the menu represented anything related to a soul food restaurant with a black "southern" owner. And to be clear it's not about race or anything. I simply dont want to eat poached eggs on brioch toast from a soul food restaurant who claims to be global, but is clearly catering to the pallet of their more caucasian demographic. Thanks hard pass for me Tho. I'd rather eat at ihop!!
Great comfort food at reasonable prices. The staff is great, friendly and professional in a "Brooklyn fashion" way. Love the place.

Excellent food, and a warm welcoming vibe--plus live music on some evenings--make this cozy spot, which is tucked away on a block that doesn't get a lot of pedestrian or car traffic but is very close to Prospect Park and Grand Army Plaza, an absolute gem.

The 3 stars not for the food .,,luv the food & drinks there but customer service sucks. Staff are so rude, sharp, short,disrespectful,ill mannered, discourteous,crass I can go on. Sometimes I really want to go cuz I’m craving some Caribbean/souls food than I remembered how unpleasant the staff r and I go somewhere else.. too many great restaurants in that area for me to leave my house & spend my money and not enjoy it.. will I go there again Mayb not sure
A lovely place, friendly staff and the brunch was delicious!
Make sure to take a stop here. Gorgeous back yard here with delicious food.
Seafood was excellently prepared, However the entree was too spicy
Had the grilled salmon. Omg delicious, lived down the block from the place for years and this is the first time.
Good food, ok service

(Translated by Google) Plentiful dishes and informal climate. Beautiful also the outdoor area at the back. There are also excellent vegetarian dishes in addition to hamburgers.  (Original) Piatti abbondanti e clima informale. Bella anche la zona all'aperto sul retro. Ottimi anche i piatti vegetariani oltre agli hamburger.
A great place, great location, great food, great employees.

Food was mixed, my shrimp were overcooked but the vegetable tagine was good. They automatically added an 18% gratuity for a party of two, then left the tip line for additional tips, with a suggestion of ANOTHER 18%. Greedy.
i have always enjoyed the food here, and i’ve been for breakfast, lunch and dinner.
Just ok. Sate the hunger, hope for a better find next time.

This is the best breakfast place I have encountered in a long time! Everything is so fresh and made beautifully. Looked for a place near Brooklyn Museum and this place had a line out the door! So cozy and eclectic. We are from Buffalo, NY.. wish I could go to Cheryl’s every day!!
Great burger!
Employees and food was awesome
Enjoyed everything!!! Food was out of this world!
Great service
Best pancakes in brooklyn

Cheryl's never disappoints. Except when it's too cold or wet to sit in that delicious backyard. Heh. But seriously, I've always been happy and me wife more so. Check that! They sometimes run out of those chilli plum wings on busy weekend afternoons and I cry buckets. Also, lovely people work there and it becomes hard sometimes to walk those 300 yards home to feed four needy cats. And the backyard - in season - is magic land.

Updated Review: 18 percent GRATUITY IS AUTOMATICALLY INCLUDED IN YOUR CHECK for two people !!! I loved Cheryl’s in the past but the food has changed and so has the service . Today I walked into the restaurant with my partner at around 4:40 and sat down because I didn’t see a hostess . After sitting a waiter gave us a drink menu and said the food wouldn’t be served until 5:00 so we ordered drinks and waited . At 5:00 the restaurant began to fill up and about 5 more parties came in after us . All of those parties received dinner menus before us , were able to place orders before us and received their dinner before my partner and I as well . My partner and I felt unfairly treated at a restaurant that we always loved to frequent in the past. Our waitress did not come back to check on us after we recieve our food and the food was subpar. The food lacked its original seasoning and my partner received a smaller sized portion of meat than I did , which left him feeling unsatisfied with his meal . To make matters worse the automatically included gratuity can be a bit pricy and increase your bill a substantial amount . The service and the food was subpar and I probably won’t return again.  First Review:  This restaurant is small and very quite. My lunch companion pointed out to me that the restaurant has a very unique but refreshing  decor. The hostess greeted us immediately and we were seated in like five minutes. The food was affordable and very delicious . During my first visit I had breakfast like eggs ,toast, bacon and orange juice. Last night I had the grilled jerk wings with scotch bonnet pepper sauce on the side, grilled salmon with mash potatoes and string beans , and fried catfish , macaroni and cheese and spinach . The food was filling , and I felt very light afterwards. My date and I were super satisfied with our meals. I would recommend this restaurant to anyone who is looking for a delicious meal, and likes comfy cozy restaurants.
The food was very good, service was good, but a gratuity was added to my bill  without notice. I don't mind if it's a party of 6 or more but I was alone

Staff was friendly. Food was ok. They added an automatic 18% tip for 2 people which seemed odd. Baked chicken had no sides, had to order separately and they forgot my spinach. The happy hour drinks were incredibly watered down. The place seemed very busy so maybe I was the only one with a bad experience. It was small and tight inside, great music playing tho.

Been here for dinner a few times. They don't take reservations so there can be a short wait. The food is always fantastic. I haven't had anything I didn't enjoy. The cocktails are great and the atmosphere is lovely.
Worth the wait! And there will be a wait. Delicious food and drinks. Pre-fix menu had breakfast, coffee/tea AND mimosa/bloody Mary for~17. Crimini mushroom omelette and French toast were delicious.

Sometimes  a long wait but the food is hmm so good. I take alot of my family and friends to Cheryl's to eat and enjoy a good time. The environment is chill,  the food is great and the price is reasonable.

After 5 or 6 visits for supper, I can say, usually very good, sometimes great, occasionally just fair. This past Sunday (4/7) was only fair. Service was swell, but the food made me realize the chef was out, as was Cheryl. And then also, with a party of just 2, they automatically added 20%. This is new. AND, the check still had the full section with 15, 18, 20, 22% amounts and space to add the tip. Without saying anywhere that gratuity was included. You only knew because the bill was too high and for an inconspicuous extra line item in the total. Odd. I left it, but it made we want to reduce to 15%. Not to mention the charge was already thru. Cheryl - not good, was a big turn off. We live around the corner and you know who we are and like us, and we are so glad you are here. Hope you see this. Just some feedback.
Warm cozy restaurant with great assortment of food. Very comfortable atmosphere
Delicious and relaxing on a Monday for breakfast. Two pancakes were plenty for this chica!

We had lunch after the Frida Kahlo exhibit at the Brooklyn Museum. It was cold and rainy. The $5 cocktails we're bone warming. The wings and veggie chili were also great. Servers friendly. Other guests also great. Nice neighborhood feel
Only a block from Brooklyn Museum or Grand Army Plaza. Medium sized menu with good selection. Every thing we had was very good. Vegetable chili was one of the best I have had.

Came here once met a cool bartender and a lovely soul at the bar. This place feels intimate and organic without feeling pretentious. The calamari was fresh and delicious. The wine selection was impressive, the service was friendly, they were playing TCM on the television which was a plus for me, the crowd was diverse, and the atmosphere was very down-to-earth. I can see it being even more amazing place in the warmer months. I will be back!!
Nice experience. Kinda small but quality service.

Waited 1.5 hours for an okay brunch. Very impersonal waitress who ignored us for 10 minutes, then rushed us through our order, snatching away our menus as soon as our order was out of our mouths. All brunch specials come with a "first cup of coffee or tea and a Bloody Mary or Mimosa." However, they won't let someone swap the Bloody Mary/Mimosa for a second cup of coffee, which is illogical to me, you have to choose a juice instead if you don't want alcohol. The regular hash and lox hash weren't very good, mushy potatoes with no crisp whatsoever. Pancakes were two smallish 4 inch pancakes that were $7 and not worth the price. I got the crimini omelet, which was browned like crazy on the outside like the eggs were overdone. Why do I even try brunch places anymore?
Not bad, but nothing that set it apart. Friendly staff. Cute interior with a tiny bar that separates the staff area/kitchen. No complaint about the food, just nothing to travel about.
Good food get there early places might be packed

We were charged for 6 rather than 4 drinks. No heat for the first 40 minutes there when it's 40 degrees out and cold inside too. Soul food with global energy + surprisingly vegetarian-friendly.

Plus a entry way doormat everyone kept tripping over it was old curled and needed to be remove and replaced with a very new one. But as always the food never disappoint me and the atmosphere otherwise was great. I love Cheryl Global Soul the food is delicious.

I'm a vegetarian, so choices were limited. I ordered vegetarian chili, home fries, and pancakes. Chili was very good, highly recommended. Home fries were overcooked and dry. I ended up throwing 'em in the chili. Pancakes were thick but not too heavy. Overall it a good place to eat. -k

This was my first and last visit. The place is very small but cute. The food was good but overpriced. The servers were pleasant but never came back to check on is after we received our food. Also they attempted to add 20% tip to our bill for a party of 3 and when we noticed and asked about it, stated it was policy to add the tip when the restaurant was "busy". We asked to see where that is posted for customers to be made aware and how exactly they define "busy" (we were one of the 4 customers they had at the time but the only black customers), they could not answer & just removed it from our bill. If you are not paying attention you would never even notice the addition to your bill and continue to add an additional tip, which the service absolutely does not deserve.

Comfortable place. Was busy when I was there so took staff a bit to bring water etc. The reason I am giving 4 not 5 is lack of vegan options. Only one option was vegan (besides soup and salad) - veggie tagine and while it was good it is not something I would return for. Frier is shared meat and veggies so even mushroom burger is not truly vegetarian unless you sub fries for salad and skip cheese if you want vegan. I had a ginger tea since all desserts are dairy based which was very strong and good. Would come back for that tea. If you are a meat eater this may be a good place for you. If you are a vegan probably not so much at least food wise. Atmosphere is great. There was live music while we were there. It was good but made it hard to talk.

I took a chance and booked this ppace on a late Sat night. My friend is tied up until the late nights. We drove past the place initially because its not that noticeable on the dark street. Almost decided to go elsewhere,  but convinced ourselves to look. That was a great decision. A care pulled out of a parking spot right in front and we knew it was karma to cone here. The place is a simple nice layout and we felt immediately comfortable upon entering. We were freeted by Alexa who was also our server, and thats all she wrote! Alexa said the rum pumch was good, and we ordered 2 of them. They were fairly potent! I enjoyed that.  We ordered the chili plum wings, and the calamari to start. The wings were ok and the calamari was really good, even without the dipping chili plum, which is delicious! I decided to have the blackened catfish, which came with sauteed spinach, and mac and cheese. This was so good! The mac and cheese was amazing, and so was the spinach and the catfish. They give nice portions for you to really enjoy. My friend ordered the striped bass escovitch style, also quite delicious. We got a taste of the string beans whoch were crunchy with a flavorful sauce to it. Will order a larger size next time. Listen, this place is a little neighborhood gem thats merits multiple visits!

My boyfriend and I had an incredibly great experience here - from the drinks and food, to the service and ambiance.  It was my second time there, but my boyfriend's first, and he was impressed just as much.  Not only did the server constantly ensured that we were satisfied with our food and drinks, the owner/Chef Cheryl also happened to be there last evening, just jamming with a live band that was playing chill music (and singing with them).  It was also quite apparent how well she treats the people who work for her in the way she spoke with them to leaving the server a tip for serving her and her friends with whom she was sharing a table that evening.  It seems like a very down to earth place.  We spoke with the Chef afterward and it was great to speak with her and to witness her humility.  It was very refreshing to meet her, and the service and excellent food/drinks we had last evening is a reflection of what I imagine is her excellent leadership at the restaurant.

The food is fabulous as is the service. Good network recognized Cheryl for good reason. I enjoy fresh fish and soup. Outside seating available warm weather.  Restaurant is small. Service good. They can get slammed and backed up in kitchen. Recommend weeknight treat as Saturday wait can he long.

Cheryl's is the first place I went to for brunch when I moved to Prospect Heights. A great space and excellent service. The menu from brunch to dinner has something for everyone. A very neighborhood vibe.

This restaurant appears to have an uneven policy of asking for id. I was asked for id on a $30 brunch bill. I'm not sure why and I found it quite by a short brown haired hostess which I found odd.
